n of' b'standards by the mit x consortium, and conference announcements. it does not' b'carry advertisements, source code, patches, or questions. if you already' b'receive the usenet news group comp.windows.x.announce or the xpert mailing' b"list, you don't need to be added to the xannounce mailing list. otherwise, to" b'redistribution addresses will be accepted for this list i.e. no personal' b'addresses. if you wish to receive xannounce yourself, please contact your mail' b'administrator to set up a local redistribution list and to put you on it.' b'comp.windows.x.apps is not gatewayed to a mailing list.' b'' b'in addition, the x consortium sponsors these public lists:' b'bug-clx clx bug reports and discussions' b'x-ada x and ada' b'x11-3d people interested in x and 3d graphics' b'ximage people interested in image processing and x' b'xvideo discussion of video extensions for x' b'to subscribe to one of these lists, assuming no-one in your' b'with the subject line including the name of the list in caps and the request' b'"addition request". in the body of the message be sure to give an address for' b'your local distribution which is accessible from mit (eddie.mit.edu).' b'' b'a mailing list for topics related to open look is sponsored by greg' b'a mailing list for bugs in the publicly-available version of xview' b'source, in particular, is sponsored by sun; send for information to' b'a mailing list for topics related to motif is sponsored by kee hinckley' b'(this group is gatewayed to comp.windows.x.motif.)' b'a mailing list for topics related to the xpm pixmap-format is sponsored' b'information. b'a mailing list discussing interviews can be subscribed to by sending to' b'message containing' b'subs amiga-x11 your real name' b"a mailing list discussing parcplace's (formerly solbourne's) oi (object" b'a mailing list discussing multi-threaded xlib can be subscribed to at' b'' b'----------------------------------------------------------------------' b'' b"o'reilly and 